HEADWORD: outfox
<hw>out*fox"</hw> <pr>(out`f⟦ocr⟧ks")</pr> <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>out</ets> + <ets>fox</ets>; from the supposed cleverness of a
fox in stalking prey.]</ety> <def>To defeat or gain an advantage over
(an antagonist) by clever stratagems; to outwit; to outmaneuver; to
outsmart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outfrown</ent>⟦br⟧
